<text x="10.16" y="-76.2" size="1.778" layer="97" align="top-left">Table 7-10. Low-speed Source Electrical Characteristics
        Driver Characteristics
                Upstream Facing Port (w/cable, low-speed only): 200 - 450 pF</text>
<text x="10.16" y="-33.02" size="1.778" layer="97" align="top-left">Table 7-7. DC Electrical Characteristics
        Input Levels for Low-/full-speed
                High (Driven): Min 2.0 V
                High (floating): 2.7 - 3.6 V
                Low: Max 0.8 V
        Output Levels for Low-/full-speed
                Low: 0.0 - 0.3 V
                High (Driven):  2.8 - 3.6 V
        Decoupling Capacitance
                Upstream Facing Port Bypass Capacitance (VBUS to GND): 1.0 - 10.0 µF
        Input Capacitance for Low-/full-speed
                Transceiver edge rate control capacitance: Max 75 pF
        Terminations
                Bus Pull-up Resistor on Upstream Facing Port: 1.5 kOhm ±5%
                Bus Pull-down Resistor on Downstream Facing Port: 15 kOhm ±5%</text>
<text x="10.16" y="-25.4" size="1.778" layer="97" align="top-left">7.1.6.1 Low-speed and Full-speed Input Characteristics
        The termination must be able to charge the D+ or D- line from 0 V to VIH (min) within 2.5 µs.</text>
<text x="10.16" y="-12.7" size="1.778" layer="97" align="top-left">7.1.5.1 Low-/Full-speed Device Speed Identification
        Low-speed devices are terminated as shown in Figure 7-21 with the pull-up resistor on the D- line.
        A device that has a detachable cable must use a 1.5 kΩ ±5% resistor tied to a voltage source between 3.0 V and 3.6 V (VTERM) to satisfy these requirements.
        Devices with captive cables may use alternative termination means. However, the Thevenin resistance of any termination must be no less than 900 Ω.</text>
<text x="10.16" y="-137.16" size="1.778" layer="97" align="top-left">Table 4-28 Sink CC Termination (Rd) Requirements
        ± 10% resistor to GND: 5.1 kΩ</text>
<text x="10.16" y="-121.92" size="1.778" layer="97" align="top-left">Table 4-27 Source CC Termination (Rp) Requirements
        Resistor pull-up to 4.75 – 5.5 V
                Default USB Power: 56 kΩ ± 20%
                1.5 A @ 5 V: 22 kΩ ± 5%
                3.0 A @ 5 V: 10 kΩ ± 5%</text>
<text x="5.08" y="-88.9" size="1.778" layer="97" align="top-left">USB Type-C® Cable and Connector Specification (Release 2.4 / October 2024)
https://www.usb.org/document-library/usb-type-cr-cable-and-connector-specification-release-24</text>
